Please add helpful links and information supporting 'Module 2 - Climate System' to this page!

* [Understanding the long-term carbon-cycle: weathering of rocks - a vitally important carbon-sink](http://skepticalscience.com/weathering.html) - Skeptical Science article by John Mason
* [A rough guide to the components of Earth's Climate System](http://skepticalscience.com/earths-climate-system.html) - Skeptical Science article by John Mason
* [The Biggest Control Knob: Carbon Dioxide in Earth's Climate History](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RffPSrRpq_g) - Lecture by Richard Alley, Penn State
* [Real Climate](http://www.realclimate.org/index.php/archives/2007/05/start-here/) A web page with commentary on climate science by climate scientists and a treasure trove of links/resources.
* [Visual Earth: Milankovitch Cycles](http://web.mit.edu/unity3d/milankovitch/) - simulation game from MIT ARTEMiS
